<h1>Starman Service Manager Documentation</h1>

<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>The <code>Comserv::Util::StarmanServiceManager</code> utility provides web-safe Starman service management capabilities. This utility focuses on operations that can be performed safely from a web interface without requiring interactive sudo commands, while providing clear instructions for system administrators when elevated privileges are needed.</p>

<h2>Key Features</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Web-Safe Operations</strong>: Service management without requiring sudo from web interface</li>
<li><strong>Comprehensive Status Reporting</strong>: Detailed service state analysis</li>
<li><strong>Process Information</strong>: Real-time process monitoring and diagnostics</li>
<li><strong>Actionable Recommendations</strong>: Intelligent suggestions for service issues</li>
<li><strong>Integration with Diagnostics</strong>: Works with StarmanDiagnostics utility</li>
<li><strong>Safe Error Handling</strong>: Graceful handling of permission and system errors</li>
</ul>

<h2>File Location</h2>
<pre>/Comserv/lib/Comserv/Util/StarmanServiceManager.pm</pre>

<h2>Dependencies</h2>
<ul>
<li>Moose - Object-oriented framework</li>
<li>Try::Tiny - Exception handling</li>
<li>POSIX - System utilities and time formatting</li>
<li>File::Spec - Cross-platform path handling</li>
<li>File::Path - Directory operations</li>
<li>Cwd - Current working directory</li>
<li>Comserv::Util::StarmanDiagnostics - Service diagnostics</li>
</ul>

<h2>Core Attributes</h2>

<h3>logger</h3>
<p>Optional logging object for operation tracking:</p>
<pre>has 'logger' =&gt; (
    is =&gt; 'rw',
    isa =&gt; 'Object',
    required =&gt; 0,
);</pre>

<h3>diagnostics</h3>
<p>Lazy-loaded StarmanDiagnostics instance for service analysis:</p>
<pre>has 'diagnostics' =&gt; (
    is =&gt; 'ro',
    isa =&gt; 'Comserv::Util::StarmanDiagnostics',
    lazy =&gt; 1,
    default =&gt; sub {
        require Comserv::Util::StarmanDiagnostics;
        return Comserv::Util::StarmanDiagnostics-&gt;new();
    }
);</pre>

<h2>Core Methods</h2>

<h3>get_service_status($app_root)</h3>
<p>Retrieves comprehensive service status information in a web-safe manner.</p>

<p><strong>Parameters:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><code>$app_root</code> - Application root directory path</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Returns:</strong> HashRef with detailed service information:</p>
<pre>{
    timestamp =&gt; '2025-01-15 10:30:00',
    service_state =&gt; 'running|stopped|unknown',
    process_info =&gt; {
        pid =&gt; 12345,
        cpu_usage =&gt; '2.5%',
        memory_usage =&gt; '150MB',
        uptime =&gt; '2 days, 3 hours'
    },
    recommendations =&gt; [
        'Service is running normally',
        'Consider restarting if memory usage is high'
    ],
    available_actions =&gt; [
        'check_logs',
        'view_configuration',
        'test_connectivity'
    ]
}</pre>

<h3>Service State Detection</h3>
<p>The service manager uses multiple methods to determine service state:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Process Detection</strong>: Checks for running Starman processes</li>
<li><strong>Port Monitoring</strong>: Verifies service is listening on configured ports</li>
<li><strong>PID File Checking</strong>: Validates PID files if present</li>
<li><strong>Response Testing</strong>: Tests service responsiveness</li>
</ul>

<h2>Web-Safe Operations</h2>

<h3>Status Checking</h3>
<p>Operations that can be performed without elevated privileges:</p>
<ul>
<li>Process status checking</li>
<li>Port availability testing</li>
<li>Log file reading (if accessible)</li>
<li>Configuration file validation</li>
<li>Resource usage monitoring</li>
</ul>

<h3>Information Gathering</h3>
<p>Safe information collection includes:</p>
<ul>
<li>Service configuration details</li>
<li>Process resource usage</li>
<li>Network connectivity status</li>
<li>Application file integrity</li>
<li>System resource availability</li>
</ul>

<h2>Recommendations System</h2>

<p>The service manager provides intelligent recommendations based on service state:</p>

<h3>Running Service Recommendations</h3>
<ul>
<li>Performance optimization suggestions</li>
<li>Resource usage warnings</li>
<li>Configuration improvement tips</li>
<li>Maintenance scheduling advice</li>
</ul>

<h3>Stopped Service Recommendations</h3>
<ul>
<li>Startup troubleshooting steps</li>
<li>Configuration validation checks</li>
<li>Dependency verification</li>
<li>System administrator contact information</li>
</ul>

<h3>Unknown State Recommendations</h3>
<ul>
<li>Diagnostic steps to determine actual state</li>
<li>Permission checking procedures</li>
<li>Alternative monitoring methods</li>
<li>Escalation procedures</li>
</ul>

<h2>Available Actions</h2>

<p>The service manager identifies actions available to the current user:</p>

<h3>User-Level Actions</h3>
<ul>
<li><code>check_logs</code> - View accessible log files</li>
<li><code>view_configuration</code> - Display service configuration</li>
<li><code>test_connectivity</code> - Test service connectivity</li>
<li><code>validate_files</code> - Check application file integrity</li>
</ul>

<h3>Admin-Level Actions</h3>
<ul>
<li><code>restart_service</code> - Restart Starman service</li>
<li><code>stop_service</code> - Stop Starman service</li>
<li><code>start_service</code> - Start Starman service</li>
<li><code>reload_configuration</code> - Reload service configuration</li>
</ul>

<h2>Integration with StarmanDiagnostics</h2>

<p>The service manager integrates closely with the StarmanDiagnostics utility:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Process Detection</strong>: Uses diagnostics for process identification</li>
<li><strong>Health Checking</strong>: Leverages diagnostic health checks</li>
<li><strong>Performance Monitoring</strong>: Utilizes diagnostic performance metrics</li>
<li><strong>Error Analysis</strong>: Incorporates diagnostic error detection</li>
</ul>

<h2>Error Handling</h2>

<h3>Permission Errors</h3>
<p>Graceful handling of permission-related issues:</p>
<ul>
<li>Clear error messages for insufficient privileges</li>
<li>Alternative information gathering methods</li>
<li>Instructions for system administrators</li>
<li>Fallback to read-only operations</li>
</ul>

<h3>System Errors</h3>
<p>Robust handling of system-level problems:</p>
<ul>
<li>Network connectivity issues</li>
<li>File system access problems</li>
<li>Process communication failures</li>
<li>Resource exhaustion scenarios</li>
</ul>

<h2>Security Considerations</h2>

<h3>Privilege Separation</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Web-Safe Design</strong>: No operations requiring elevated privileges</li>
<li><strong>Read-Only Operations</strong>: Focus on information gathering</li>
<li><strong>Safe Defaults</strong>: Conservative approach to system interaction</li>
</ul>

<h3>Information Disclosure</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Filtered Output</strong>: Sensitive information is filtered</li>
<li><strong>Access Control</strong>: Respects file system permissions</li>
<li><strong>Error Sanitization</strong>: Error messages don't reveal system details</li>
</ul>

<h2>Usage Examples</h2>

<h3>Basic Service Status Check</h3>
<pre>use Comserv::Util::StarmanServiceManager;

my $service_manager = Comserv::Util::StarmanServiceManager-&gt;new();
my $status = $service_manager-&gt;get_service_status('/path/to/app');

if ($status-&gt;{service_state} eq 'running') {
    print "Service is running normally\n";
    print "PID: " . $status-&gt;{process_info}-&gt;{pid} . "\n";
} else {
    print "Service issues detected\n";
    print "Recommendations:\n";
    for my $rec (@{$status-&gt;{recommendations}}) {
        print "  - $rec\n";
    }
}</pre>

<h3>Controller Integration</h3>
<pre># In a controller
sub service_status : Local {
    my ($self, $c) = @_;
    
    my $service_manager = Comserv::Util::StarmanServiceManager-&gt;new(
        logger =&gt; $self-&gt;logging
    );
    
    my $status = $service_manager-&gt;get_service_status($c-&gt;config-&gt;{home});
    
    $c-&gt;stash(
        service_status =&gt; $status,
        template =&gt; 'admin/service_status.tt'
    );
}</pre>

<h2>Configuration</h2>

<p>The service manager uses configuration from multiple sources:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Application Config</strong>: Catalyst application configuration</li>
<li><strong>System Config</strong>: System service configuration files</li>
<li><strong>Environment Variables</strong>: Runtime environment settings</li>
<li><strong>Default Values</strong>: Built-in sensible defaults</li>
</ul>

<h2>Performance Considerations</h2>

<h3>Efficient Operations</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Lazy Loading</strong>: Diagnostics loaded only when needed</li>
<li><strong>Caching</strong>: Status information cached for short periods</li>
<li><strong>Minimal System Calls</strong>: Optimized system interaction</li>
<li><strong>Timeout Handling</strong>: Operations have reasonable timeouts</li>
</ul>

<h3>Resource Management</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Memory Efficient</strong>: Minimal memory footprint</li>
<li><strong>CPU Conscious</strong>: Low CPU usage for status checks</li>
<li><strong>Network Aware</strong>: Minimal network operations</li>
</ul>

